# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js App Router project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Package
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` version 1.6.1 using npm
- Updated `package.json` to include the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the resolved dependency tree

### 2. Modified Files

#### `src/app/layout.tsx`
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag after `{children}`
- Preserved all existing code structure, styling, and functionality

## Implementation Details

The Analytics component was placed in the root layout file following Next.js App Router best practices:
- Located in `src/app/layout.tsx` (the root layout for the app directory)
- Positioned after `{children}` within the `<body>` tag
- This ensures analytics tracking is enabled across all pages of the application

## Verification Steps Completed

1. ✅ Package installation successful
2. ✅ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
3. ✅ Linting passed for modified file (no new errors introduced)
4. ✅ All changes staged with git

## Notes

- The project uses npm as the package manager (confirmed by presence of package-lock.json)
- The build generated static pages successfully for all routes (/, /hospitals, /national)
- No breaking changes were introduced
- The Analytics component will automatically collect anonymous usage data when deployed to Vercel
- Pre-existing linting errors in other files were not addressed as they were outside the scope of this task
